      35             : 
      36             : /*
      37             :  * This module converts keysym values into the corresponding ISO 10646
      38             :  * (UCS, Unicode) values.
      39             :  *
      40             :  * The array keysymtab[] contains pairs of X11 keysym values for graphical
      41             :  * characters and the corresponding Unicode value. The function
      42             :  * _glfwKeySym2Unicode() maps a keysym onto a Unicode value using a binary
      43             :  * search, therefore keysymtab[] must remain SORTED by keysym value.
      44             :  *
      45             :  * We allow to represent any UCS character in the range U-00000000 to
      46             :  * U-00FFFFFF by a keysym value in the range 0x01000000 to 0x01ffffff.
      47             :  * This admittedly does not cover the entire 31-bit space of UCS, but
      48             :  * it does cover all of the characters up to U-10FFFF, which can be
      49             :  * represented by UTF-16, and more, and it is very unlikely that higher
      50             :  * UCS codes will ever be assigned by ISO. So to get Unicode character
      51             :  * U+ABCD you can directly use keysym 0x0100abcd.
      52             :  *
      53             :  * Original author: Markus G. Kuhn <mkuhn@acm.org>, University of
      54             :  *                  Cambridge, April 2001
      55             :  *
      56             :  * Special thanks to Richard Verhoeven <river@win.tue.nl> for preparing
      57             :  * an initial draft of the mapping table.
      58             :  *
      59             :  */
      60             : 
      61             : /*
      62             :  * For Xenolith, only LINUX guard define added, no other changes
      63             :  */
      64             : 
      65             : //************************************************************************
      66             : //****                KeySym to Unicode mapping table                 ****
      67             : //************************************************************************
